holiday two years later.

02:47.300 --> 02:48.819
That looks good, what's that?

02:48.820 --> 02:51.099
I sort of wish I'd ordered that.

02:51.100 --> 02:55.099
Our invisible desserts have arrived!

02:55.300 --> 02:58.619
I know we weren't happy that second
week of our marriage, Douglas,

02:58.620 --> 03:00.859
but give us another chance, as a couple.

03:00.860 --> 03:03.139
I don't know.

03:03.140 --> 03:06.899
I don't think we can just
pick up from where we left off.

03:06.900 --> 03:10.539
No, Victoria, I'm sorry, it's over.

03:13.460 --> 03:16.419
Oh God!

03:16.420 --> 03:19.779
I forgot you could do that.

03:19.780 --> 03:23.779
Maybe we should give it another go!

03:25.260 --> 03:27.859
Nnngh...

03:27.860 --> 03:30.379
Well that is new!

03:30.380 --> 03:31.619
How are you doing that?

03:31.620 --> 03:35.619
That might be the dog.

03:36.020 --> 03:37.539
Heston!

03:37.540 --> 03:39.659
I'd like to introduce you to my...

03:39.660 --> 03:43.659
Wi-i-i-ife.

03:46.420 --> 03:50.219
I want to divorce my wife.

03:50.220 --> 03:51.259
Why are you telling me?

03:51.260 --> 03:52.819
Aren't you with legal?

03:52.820 --> 03:54.739
No.

03:54.740 --> 03:56.099
Remind me?

03:56.100 --> 03:58.899
IT. Relationship manager.

03:58.900 --> 04:02.419
Ah. Well then I probably shouldn't
have told you any of that.

04:02.420 --> 04:04.059
Anyway...

04:04.060 --> 04:06.459
I want to divorce her right now.

04:06.460 --> 04:08.859
Now's too late. Before now.

04:08.860 --> 04:11.979
