07:59.340 --> 08:01.619
She won.

08:01.620 --> 08:04.499
I'm still paying costs.

08:04.500 --> 08:08.499
"Pedal stool"!

08:10.460 --> 08:12.819
212 million quid!

08:12.820 --> 08:14.859
You can't be serious!

08:14.860 --> 08:16.859
Oh, we're quite serious, Mr. Reynholm.

08:16.860 --> 08:20.139
But that's enough to bring
Reynholm Industries to its knees!

08:20.140 --> 08:23.659
Bloody blast, this is up my arse!

08:23.660 --> 08:26.699
That is the amount, it
is not up for negotiation.

08:26.700 --> 08:29.859
Balls from hell, you shit-twins!

08:29.860 --> 08:31.099
Calm down, Mr. Reynholm.

08:31.100 --> 08:33.899
Bollocks to be telling me
to calm down, my old chap.

08:33.900 --> 08:37.899
She wants 220 titty million quid
and you tell me to calm down!

08:38.020 --> 08:39.259
You're fired.

08:39.260 --> 08:40.299
I'm not your lawyer.

08:40.299 --> 08:43.619
Piss off! I'm going to represent myself.

08:43.620 --> 08:45.859
I'm not your lawyer.

08:45.860 --> 08:47.899
You sit there, all confident.

08:47.900 --> 08:51.659
Yeah? But when this goes to Court,
that's when the talking stops.

08:51.660 --> 08:53.459
Mr. Reynholm,

08:53.460 --> 08:55.859
there might actually be
more talking in Court,

08:55.860 --> 08:59.499
this would actually be a comparatively small
amount of talking, what we're doing here.

08:59.500 --> 09:00.419
Oh, I see.

09:00.420 --> 09:00.979
Sorry.

09:00.980 --> 09:04.419
Sorry. No, that's all right,
it's what I pay you for.

09:04.420 --> 09:06.019
Look at her. Cold as ice.

09:06.020 --> 09:10.019
But I tell you this, behind
those shades, she's terrified.

09:16.140 --> 09:18.539
One thing you should
know about me, Jen...

09:18.540 --> 09:21.699
When I put my mind to
something, it gets done.

09:21.700 --> 09:25.299
Representing myself is the
kind of challenge I relish.

09:25.300 --> 09:27.539
Well, you'll have to
do a lot of preparation.

09:27.540 --> 09:30.219
Bring it on!

09:51.980 --> 09:54.499
What's this?

09:54.500 --> 09:57.899
It's my suit. I made it
myself. Took me a few days!

09:57.900 --> 10:00.619
How did you find time
to prepare for the trial?

10:00.620 --> 10:03.419
How did I what?

10:03.420 --> 10:06.339
Mrs. Reynholm, you saythat in
the short time you were married,

10:06.340 --> 10:09.179
you became indispensable
to Mr. Reynholm...

10:09.180 --> 10:11.739
in what way were you indispensable?

10:11.740 --> 10:13.539
I had to brush his teeth.

10:13.540 --> 10:14.779
Really?

10:14.780 --> 10:15.979
Yes.

10:15.980 --> 10:17.339
That's not an expression?

10:17.340 --> 10:18.619
No.

10:18.620 --> 10:19.859
You got the brush,

10:19.860 --> 10:22.579
you applied toothpaste to it,

10:22.580 --> 10:25.419
you moved it into his mouth...

10:25.420 --> 10:29.419
and moved your hand up and down.

10:29.820 --> 10:31.779
Well, if I didn't do
it, he wouldn't do it.

10:31.780 --> 10:35.379
Well, if I didn't do it, he wouldn't
do it. Make a note... "brush teeth".

10:35.380 --> 10:38.219
Now, you're asking for
quite a large amount.

10:38.220 --> 10:40.019
I think it is an appropriate amount.

10:40.020 --> 10:41.659
Bollocks.

10:41.660 --> 10:42.939
Mr. Reynholm.

10:42.940 --> 10:45.499
Yes, your honour?

10:45.500 --> 10:49.499
