kissed me on my bottom, Your Honour.

14:44.620 --> 14:47.299
I see.

14:47.300 --> 14:49.739
I'm sure you can
understand my discomfort.

14:49.740 --> 14:52.099
Are you all right? Can you continue?

14:52.100 --> 14:54.419
I can continue. Thank you.

14:54.420 --> 14:58.419
The way you tell it, your employer
sounds like a paragon of virtue.

14:59.820 --> 15:02.899
That's right. And
furthermore, I would like

15:02.900 --> 15:06.899
to say at this point that I think
this whole case to be a damp squid.

15:06.980 --> 15:09.819
Thank you, no further questions.

15:09.820 --> 15:12.339
Oooh! I have one more
question, your Honour.

15:12.340 --> 15:13.899
Yes?

15:13.900 --> 15:17.659
What did you say?

15:17.660 --> 15:18.699
What?

15:18.700 --> 15:21.819
What did you say the case was?
May I have it read back please?

15:21.820 --> 15:25.019
"I believe this entire case
to be a bit of a damp squid."

15:25.020 --> 15:27.379
"A damp squid?"

15:27.380 --> 15:29.259
What does that mean?

15:29.260 --> 15:32.899
Oh, Jen, it's an expression.

15:32.900 --> 15:35.459
It means that I believe

15:35.460 --> 15:38.659
that everything that's been said
in this case, everyone already knew.

15:38.660 --> 15:40.659
Yes, but did you say "damp squid"?

15:40.660 --> 15:42.139
That's right.

15:42.140 --> 15:44.819
Did you not mean, "damp squib"?

15:44.820 --> 15:48.059
No, it's "squid".

15:48.060 --> 15:50.699
What's a squib?

15:50.700 --> 15:53.499
